---
import { withBase } from '../../utils/paths';
import DocsLayout from '../../components/docs/DocsLayout.astro';
---

<DocsLayout
  title="Maintenance History | BMR PrintCare Docs"
  description="Maintenance history guide for BMR PrintCare, covering planned dated service records, notes, parts, and practical review limits."
  heading="Maintenance history should make past work easier to review."
  intro="This guide outlines the planned record-keeping approach for maintenance events. The exact app interface may change while BMR PrintCare remains in development."
>
  <section class="docs-section" aria-labelledby="history-purpose-title">
    <h2 id="history-purpose-title">What a maintenance record is for</h2>
    <p>
      A maintenance record is intended to capture what happened, when it happened, and why it mattered. Good records can
      help users understand repeated issues, remember replaced parts, and review past actions before making new changes.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="docs-section" aria-labelledby="record-examples-title">
    <h2 id="record-examples-title">Examples of useful notes</h2>
    <ul class="plain-list">
      <li>Cleaning, lubrication, belt checks, or visual inspections.</li>
      <li>Nozzle, tube, fan, sensor, or build surface replacement notes.</li>
      <li>Symptoms observed before maintenance and results observed afterward.</li>
      <li>Parts, consumables, or settings that may be useful to remember later.</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <section class="docs-section" aria-labelledby="record-tone-title">
    <h2 id="record-tone-title">Keep records practical</h2>
    <p>
      The most useful notes are usually short, specific, and dated. BMR PrintCare is not planned as an automatic
      diagnostic system, so users should still rely on careful inspection, official guidance, and responsible repair
      practices.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="content-panel" aria-labelledby="history-next-title">
    <h2 id="history-next-title">Related documentation</h2>
    <ul class="link-list">
      <li><a href={withBase('/docs/preventive-maintenance/')}>Understand preventive maintenance</a></li>
      <li><a href={withBase('/docs/parts-and-consumables/')}>Track parts and consumables</a></li>
      <li><a href={withBase('/roadmap/')}>Review roadmap-only topics</a></li>
    </ul>
  </section>
</DocsLayout>
